 The smell is believed to be coming from Boskrans wastewater treatment works. The disgusting smell has been engulfing  various parts of Middelburg, with areas most affected being Dennesig and Kanonkop, since Sunday. Geese have no choice but to swim in the Klein Olifants, contaminated by waste water from Boskrans. As a result, residents are frustrated at the inability by the municipality to solve the problem – which has been ongoing for years. Read: Waste water killing Klein Olifants This is how some residents reacted on social media:  • Deirdre Grobler Cloete: Jip. Dis bitter erg. Mens kan nie lewe met die vrot stink reuk nie • Elma Hennings Snyder: Dit is erg, ek kry skoon hoofpyn van daai stank • Morne Herselman: Dit is nie danksy die wind nie, dis danksy die k*k stadsraad wat nog nooit rioolstelsels opgradeer het nie… Het gister op die Loskop pad uit gery en die stank gevang, dis baie erg. • Nicolene Claassen Smith: Niemand het gesê dis die wind se skuld nie… ons sê dat as die wind waai is dit erg. Ons weet wat die oorsaak is •Send your comment to yaseen@mobserver.co.za. Read: Video – What is happening at Boskrans?